# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 6)

Phase 6 will push our Local Data Persistence to the next level by implementing **Full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) capability** across the application. Instead of just persisting toggle switches, the app will allow the user to actually *generate new data*.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dynamic Meals (`AddMeal.tsx` → `Meals.tsx`)
Currently, clicking "Save Meal" just returns the user back to the Meals tab. We will:
- Establish a `hercare_custom_meals` array in local storage.
- Update `AddMeal.tsx` with a stateful form that actively pushes a new meal object to this array.
- Update `Meals.tsx` to dynamically `map` through and render these newly created meals alongside the defaults.

### 2. Dynamic Notes (`NoteEditor.tsx` → `Notes.tsx`)
Currently, `Notes.tsx` renders static cards. We will:
- Establish a `hercare_user_notes` array in local storage.
- Update `NoteEditor.tsx` to capture the Title and Body input on "Save", generating a new Note object with a date.
- Update `Notes.tsx` to dynamically render user-generated notes at the bottom of the screen.

### 3. Dynamic Shifts (`ShiftDetails.tsx`)
Currently, the shift calendar is static. We will:
- Introduce logic to add a completely custom shift to a `hercare_scheduled_shifts` local storage array.
- Render these upcoming configured shifts on `ShiftDetails.tsx`.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> The focus of this phase is taking the prototype from simply "remembering buttons clicked" to "allowing real content generation" (adding a real customized note or a real custom meal). Do you agree with upgrading these flows to be fully dynamic as our Phase 6?

